summary: As a teacher of English and Dutch and as a Feuerstein trainer I greatly believe in the importance of paying attention to the student's individual questions and the necessity to observe and listen closely to what the student does and says. This way I often discover the student's thinking process and can help him or her take the next step towards independent learning. This is the ultimate goal: to provide the student with the necessary strategies to become an independent learner.
